<div id="review_1590602410" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1590602410" />
    <a title="L.S. Popovich" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4567704-l-s-popovich"><img alt="L.S. Popovich" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1537455199p2/4567704.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1590602410?book_show_action=true">Jun 25, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="L.S. Popovich" class="user" itemprop="url" name="L.S. Popovich" href="/user/show/4567704-l-s-popovich">L.S. Popovich</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4567704-l-s-popovich?shelf=3-star">3-star</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4567704-l-s-popovich?shelf=epic-fantasy">epic-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4567704-l-s-popovich?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4567704-l-s-popovich?shelf=2021">2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4567704-l-s-popovich?shelf=audiobook-greats">audiobook-greats</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4567704-l-s-popovich?shelf=british-irish-welsh-scottish">british-irish-welsh-scottish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4567704-l-s-popovich?shelf=united-kingdom">united-kingdom</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1590602410" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11065860217378292831">While Moorcock&apos;s oeuvre is comparable to that of Vance, Silverberg, Zelazny, and any other Golden Age master of fantasy, I liked Corum better. You might also try Robert E. Howard, who is always better than you are expecting. Though I enjoyed Elric&apos;s tale, there was a lot of telling instead of showing. I&apos;m okay with this when the information is compelling. The information here was merely adequate. I was not enraptured by the grandiose world building. It did not congeal. But the next books in the </span>
  <span id="freeText11065860217378292831" style="display:none">While Moorcock's oeuvre is comparable to that of Vance, Silverberg, Zelazny, and any other Golden Age master of fantasy, I liked Corum better. You might also try Robert E. Howard, who is always better than you are expecting. Though I enjoyed Elric's tale, there was a lot of telling instead of showing. I'm okay with this when the information is compelling. The information here was merely adequate. I was not enraptured by the grandiose world building. It did not congeal. But the next books in the series doubtless solve that problem. The author's mode of communication in this book was fairly basic. Just like in Corum, he includes such well-worn story beats that it is easy to come away unimpressed when you've become jaded by a thousand Hollywoodizations. An unusual choice for a protagonist, but far from the polarizing main character in Lord Foul's Bane. Elric inhabits a middle ground, relatable enough, but still slightly uncomfortable. Overall, an easy, quick, dreamily memorable read. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11065860217378292831" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


